1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,790
There's something I'd like to confirm.

2
00:00:01,790 --> 00:00:05,270
The rumor
that one of our teachers is acting unusually,

3
00:00:05,270 --> 00:00:06,850
is true.

4
00:00:06,850 --> 00:00:08,240
My name is Solar.

5
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:10,500
I'm the homeroom teacher of Grade 2, Class 1.

6
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:13,530
But on the day of the parents' meeting,
I'll be Sun.

7
00:00:13,530 --> 00:00:17,300
Actually, my concern is
not only Teacher Solar,

8
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:19,530
but also Teacher Pobmek.

9
00:00:19,530 --> 00:00:22,060
I apologize to all the parents

10
00:00:22,060 --> 00:00:24,560
for not having a teaching license yet.

11
00:00:24,560 --> 00:00:26,920
I'll allow this for one year only.

12
00:00:26,920 --> 00:00:30,470
I hope the teachers with issues
will be able to sort themselves out.

13
00:00:30,470 --> 00:00:32,650
Thank you, Ms. Pang.

14
00:00:32,650 --> 00:00:34,320
Let me hug you.

15
00:00:38,450 --> 00:00:39,740
So nice.

16
00:00:39,740 --> 00:00:42,340
I feel twice as encouraged now.

17
00:00:45,390 --> 00:00:46,820
C.

18
00:00:50,110 --> 00:00:51,890
A minor.

19
00:00:53,691 --> 00:00:56,621
D minor, then G.

20
00:01:01,100 --> 00:01:02,900
This is weird, man.

21
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:04,810
You used to be able to do this.

22
00:01:04,810 --> 00:01:07,060
Why did you suddenly quit?

23
00:01:10,879 --> 00:01:12,870
No reason.

24
00:01:12,870 --> 00:01:15,020
School just got intense,

25
00:01:15,020 --> 00:01:17,060
so I stopped playing.

26
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:19,780
It's alright.

27
00:01:19,780 --> 00:01:23,520
Just keep practicing,
and it'll come back to you.

28
00:01:32,670 --> 00:01:34,700
Hello, Mom.

29
00:01:34,700 --> 00:01:35,780
What?

30
00:01:35,780 --> 00:01:37,710
You're at my condo?

31
00:01:37,710 --> 00:01:40,300
Oh? You're not home?

32
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:43,380
But I keep hearing some noises.

33
00:01:43,380 --> 00:01:45,090
Something's not right.

34
00:01:45,090 --> 00:01:47,120
I'm scared it might be a thief.

35
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:49,330
It's not a thief, Mom.

36
00:01:51,635 --> 00:01:53,130
Oh, ma'am.

37
00:01:53,130 --> 00:01:54,500
Hello.

38
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:55,940
Oh.

39
00:01:55,940 --> 00:01:58,220
So you're the maintenance guy?

40
00:02:07,520 --> 00:02:08,770
Pobmek!

41
00:02:08,770 --> 00:02:10,660
I've got everything set just right.

42
00:02:10,660 --> 00:02:12,250
Can you not mess with it?

43
00:02:12,250 --> 00:02:13,540
Gosh, Jee!

44
00:02:13,540 --> 00:02:15,990
Can you stop obsessing over this
for a second?

45
00:02:15,990 --> 00:02:18,540
I'm freaking stressed right now!

46
00:02:18,540 --> 00:02:22,100
Huh? Why are you so stressed?

47
00:02:24,359 --> 00:02:27,246
I haven't told my mom...

48
00:02:27,246 --> 00:02:30,090
that I'm dating a guy.

49
00:03:30,100 --> 00:03:31,441
Well...

50
00:03:31,441 --> 00:03:32,900
Don't worry.

51
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:34,960
Please continue working.

52
00:03:42,060 --> 00:03:44,300
Well...

53
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:45,700
I'm not a maintenance guy.

54
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:47,930
So you're with condo management.

55
00:03:47,930 --> 00:03:50,310
Don't mind me.

56
00:03:50,310 --> 00:03:54,800
I'm just here to surprise my son
and his partner today.

57
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:57,736
He's worked really hard
and was able to afford a nice condo,

58
00:03:57,736 --> 00:03:59,860
so I just wanted to come visit him.

59
00:03:59,860 --> 00:04:02,440
And I want to meet his partner.

60
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:04,940
I want to see if she's pretty.

61
00:04:17,140 --> 00:04:19,950
My mom is super strict.

62
00:04:19,950 --> 00:04:22,690
She never accepts anything easily.

63
00:04:27,890 --> 00:04:30,550
Is that a girl or a boy?

64
00:04:30,550 --> 00:04:31,660
Mom!

65
00:04:31,660 --> 00:04:33,980
Kids these days are weird.

66
00:04:33,980 --> 00:04:36,510
That's why I take good care of my son.

67
00:04:36,510 --> 00:04:38,470
I made sure he's in a good environment

68
00:04:38,470 --> 00:04:40,530
and chose the right faculty for him.

69
00:04:40,530 --> 00:04:42,500
You're studying accounting, right?

70
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:44,870
Do you like it?

71
00:04:44,870 --> 00:04:46,603
Well, I...

72
00:04:46,603 --> 00:04:48,380
Of course, he likes it.

73
00:04:48,380 --> 00:04:51,020
Good university, good environment.

74
00:04:51,020 --> 00:04:53,000
I even put him in the on-campus dorm.

75
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:57,500
Who knows what he'd face
if I let him live elsewhere on his own?

76
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:01,740
Is it really that bad?

77
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:03,700
Yeah.

78
00:05:03,700 --> 00:05:07,480
Not to mention, she used to
call me every day when I was in school.

79
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:10,590
If it was out of concern,
I wouldn't mind at all.

80
00:05:10,590 --> 00:05:13,770
But it felt more like
she was trying to find fault with me.

81
00:05:13,770 --> 00:05:16,680
But from what I've seen of your mom
since I was a kid,

82
00:05:17,580 --> 00:05:20,530
I don't think she's that strict.

83
00:05:20,530 --> 00:05:22,140
My mom?

84
00:05:23,970 --> 00:05:25,900
How do you see her?

85
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:31,740
She seems pretty modern,
lives in the present,

86
00:05:31,740 --> 00:05:32,890
and knows a lot about new things.

87
00:05:32,890 --> 00:05:35,000
That's not my mom.

88
00:05:36,260 --> 00:05:39,870
But damn, I have no idea...

89
00:05:40,700 --> 00:05:44,750
if she'll be okay with me dating Solar.

90
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:46,980
That's right.

91
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:50,690
I'm Pobmek's boyfriend. My name is Solar.

92
00:05:54,260 --> 00:05:56,370
Oh!

93
00:05:56,370 --> 00:05:58,690
We finally met!

94
00:06:05,570 --> 00:06:07,950
This is just like a BL series!

95
00:06:07,950 --> 00:06:10,970
You two are so cute!

96
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:14,270
Thank you. Would you like something to drink?

97
00:06:14,270 --> 00:06:16,390
Yeah, sure.

98
00:06:16,390 --> 00:06:17,820
Here you go.

99
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,690
Want some, Solar?

100
00:06:36,690 --> 00:06:39,800
Not right now. Thank you.

101
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:41,656
If I didn't have a son,

102
00:06:41,656 --> 00:06:46,770
I'd be sipping beer by the pool,
not worrying about anyone by now.

103
00:06:46,770 --> 00:06:47,900
Oh?

104
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:50,623
Why don't you try that?

105
00:06:51,733 --> 00:06:53,890
You're right.

106
00:06:53,890 --> 00:07:00,010
But I gave up a lot of things I liked
when I had Pobmek.

107
00:07:03,340 --> 00:07:07,207
By the way,
Pobmek loves steamed crab with herbs.

108
00:07:07,207 --> 00:07:09,070
- You know that?
- Yes.

109
00:07:09,070 --> 00:07:12,010
I love making it for him when he comes home.

110
00:07:12,010 --> 00:07:14,320
But he hasn't been home in a long time.

111
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:17,780
I guess he's busy with work.

112
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:25,900
Why are you smiling?

113
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:29,450
You're so sweet and kind to Pobmek.

114
00:07:29,450 --> 00:07:32,949
I just thought you two would be very close,

115
00:07:32,949 --> 00:07:35,624
but why...

116
00:07:43,770 --> 00:07:45,280
This guitar...

117
00:07:45,280 --> 00:07:47,060
It's mine!

118
00:07:47,060 --> 00:07:48,248
Hello.

119
00:07:48,889 --> 00:07:50,850
Hi, Jee!

120
00:07:50,850 --> 00:07:52,480
What are you doing here?

121
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:55,870
Oh, I was just out running some errands
with Pobmek.

122
00:07:55,870 --> 00:07:58,600
It's so nice that
you're still friends with my son.

123
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:01,920
And we're lucky we work at the same place.

124
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:02,904
Really?

125
00:08:02,904 --> 00:08:06,310
You both work as auditors
at the same company?

126
00:08:06,310 --> 00:08:08,632
You two are really impressive.

127
00:08:13,540 --> 00:08:16,104
You're too kind.

128
00:08:24,648 --> 00:08:26,080
How have you been, Jee?

129
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:29,248
How's working as an auditor? Good?

130
00:08:33,407 --> 00:08:35,416
I enjoy it.

131
00:08:35,416 --> 00:08:36,504
That's great.

132
00:08:36,504 --> 00:08:41,256
You know,
a good job gives you stability in life.

133
00:08:43,310 --> 00:08:46,580
Do you still play guitar as a hobby?

134
00:08:46,580 --> 00:08:50,744
Solar, this reminds me of
when Pobmek was in high school.

135
00:08:50,744 --> 00:08:52,610
He used to play music, you know?

136
00:08:52,610 --> 00:08:54,064
Yeah.

137
00:08:56,070 --> 00:09:00,992
And now, our final band
in the Hot Woof Music Awards competition.

138
00:09:00,992 --> 00:09:03,518
Let's give it up for them!

139
00:09:03,518 --> 00:09:06,137
Art Attack!

140
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:15,400
[Mom]

141
00:09:20,136 --> 00:09:22,560
But he wasn't very good.

142
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:25,840
It's for the best
that he didn't waste time forcing it.

143
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:28,408
He got his act together,
focused on his studies instead,

144
00:09:28,408 --> 00:09:30,450
and got into accounting.

145
00:09:30,450 --> 00:09:32,460
- Otherwise...
- Mom.

146
00:09:33,220 --> 00:09:37,176
Let's stop talking about this.

147
00:09:46,540 --> 00:09:49,312
Aunt, would you like some dessert?

148
00:09:49,312 --> 00:09:52,072
- I can order something for you.
- Yeah, that'd be great.

149
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:54,610
Here.

150
00:09:54,610 --> 00:09:56,016
Oh.

151
00:10:02,550 --> 00:10:03,920
Let me try this.

152
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:05,784
Oh, wow!

153
00:10:05,784 --> 00:10:07,514
- It's good, right?
- Yummy.

154
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:20,272
Are you okay?

155
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,704
Yeah.

156
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:27,192
I'm trying to be.

157
00:10:29,030 --> 00:10:31,052
I'm just scared of what'll happen

158
00:10:31,052 --> 00:10:33,792
if Mom finds out you can switch with Sun,

159
00:10:35,820 --> 00:10:39,064
and that I'm an elementary school teacher.

160
00:10:40,528 --> 00:10:43,032
But your mom seems kind.

161
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:48,232
Aren't you overthinking it?

162
00:10:52,410 --> 00:10:58,232
My mom is the reason I feel this way now.

163
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:05,700
Hey, I'm heading out.

164
00:11:05,700 --> 00:11:08,840
I need to check the kids' homework.

165
00:11:12,970 --> 00:11:15,424
Oh, I mean,

166
00:11:15,424 --> 00:11:18,624
I need to check the interns' accounting work.

167
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:21,680
I'm gonna go.

168
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:26,250
Mom.

169
00:11:26,250 --> 00:11:27,768
What time are you leaving?

170
00:11:27,768 --> 00:11:29,816
I'll drop you off.

171
00:11:37,220 --> 00:11:41,050
I think I'll stay for a couple of days.

172
00:11:41,050 --> 00:11:43,704
I can sleep on the sofa. No need to worry.

173
00:11:43,704 --> 00:11:46,000
You two usually eat here, right?

174
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:49,888
Let me show off my cooking skills tomorrow.

175
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:08,880
[Sponge Bath Service]

176
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:12,760
[Jak-Ka-Jee]
Is it that bad, man?

177
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:16,220
[Principal Sodchuen]
What? What's going on?

178
00:12:16,220 --> 00:12:18,729
Tell me how to hide from my mom

179
00:12:18,729 --> 00:12:23,000
the fact that I'm a teacher.

180
00:12:26,168 --> 00:12:28,168
Lately, I've been waking up late.

181
00:12:28,168 --> 00:12:32,232
If Mom wakes up and sees Sun, I'm screwed.

182
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:39,520
[Principal Sodchuen]
Then get him out of the apartment ASAP.

183
00:12:50,110 --> 00:12:51,608
Hey, she's probably asleep.

184
00:12:51,608 --> 00:12:53,120
I think...

185
00:12:54,780 --> 00:12:56,590
Damn it!

186
00:12:56,590 --> 00:12:59,032
If I wake him up right now, he'll be Sun.

187
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:49,168
[Sponge Bath Service]

188
00:13:49,168 --> 00:13:51,464
Mission accomplished.

189
00:13:51,464 --> 00:13:55,430
Thanks for the advice.

190
00:13:55,430 --> 00:13:57,400
- Uncle.
- Whoa!

191
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:00,688
Why did you bring me here?

192
00:14:01,590 --> 00:14:05,904
Well, I brought you here to do something fun.

193
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:13,208
Don't tell me you're up to something again.

194
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:21,608
Pobmek!

195
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:45,280
[Pobmek Ekrakrak]
[Auditor]

196
00:15:11,296 --> 00:15:13,328
What a coincidence.

197
00:15:13,328 --> 00:15:15,580
Where are you going? Do you need a ride?

198
00:15:15,580 --> 00:15:18,620
I'm going to see Pobmek at the office.

199
00:15:18,620 --> 00:15:20,672
Please hop in.

200
00:15:21,990 --> 00:15:23,702
Nice.

201
00:15:26,540 --> 00:15:28,048
The seat's set at 100 degrees,

202
00:15:28,048 --> 00:15:30,112
and the distance from the front
is just right.

203
00:15:30,112 --> 00:15:33,220
Just what I'd expect from your car, Jee.

204
00:15:33,220 --> 00:15:37,760
You're the only one who gets me this well.

205
00:15:38,376 --> 00:15:43,820
But unfortunately,
I'm not going to the office today.

206
00:15:43,820 --> 00:15:46,480
Oh? Why didn't you say so?

207
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:48,740
It's alright.

208
00:15:48,740 --> 00:15:52,620
You're already in, and I'm free anyway.

209
00:15:52,620 --> 00:15:54,339
Why don't we go to the market

210
00:15:54,339 --> 00:15:56,920
and get Pobmek something delicious to eat?

211
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:01,016
That's actually a good idea.

212
00:16:01,016 --> 00:16:02,944
Let's go.

213
00:16:09,378 --> 00:16:10,793
Oh.

214
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:14,928
How's it going? All good?

215
00:16:16,580 --> 00:16:19,592
At first, it was pretty tough,
but now it's better.

216
00:16:19,592 --> 00:16:21,900
He's calmed down.

217
00:16:21,900 --> 00:16:23,544
You're good.

218
00:16:23,544 --> 00:16:25,536
You've got Sun under control now.

219
00:16:25,536 --> 00:16:27,648
Actually, no.

220
00:16:31,180 --> 00:16:34,560
Sun dug out all the snacks you hid.

221
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:39,180
Oh! My secret stash got trashed.

222
00:16:39,180 --> 00:16:41,944
May I submit the form for the talent stage?

223
00:16:41,944 --> 00:16:45,048
Please leave it on the desk, Four.

224
00:16:46,890 --> 00:16:48,820
To be honest,

225
00:16:48,820 --> 00:16:51,870
would it be okay
if Sun stayed with you for a while?

226
00:16:51,870 --> 00:16:54,660
I don't mind him staying with me.

227
00:16:54,660 --> 00:16:56,928
It's just that he might get fussy.

228
00:16:56,928 --> 00:16:59,240
He's not used to my place.

229
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:01,300
We'll just have to deal with it,

230
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:05,450
even if it means crying
or losing sleep for a couple of days.

231
00:17:05,450 --> 00:17:07,480
Otherwise, there'll be trouble.

232
00:17:09,888 --> 00:17:11,928
♫ Take it off, take it, take it off ♫

233
00:17:11,928 --> 00:17:13,912
♫ Don't hide no more, don't hide no more ♫

234
00:17:13,912 --> 00:17:15,090
Sun,

235
00:17:15,090 --> 00:17:18,140
I don't think I can give you the title of
Sigma Boy anymore,

236
00:17:18,140 --> 00:17:20,944
because you're about to
get eliminated by Teacher Pobmek.

237
00:17:20,944 --> 00:17:22,580
Huh?

238
00:17:22,580 --> 00:17:23,720
What are you guys talking about?

239
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:28,568
Four overheard that
you're going to stay with Principal Sodchuen!

240
00:17:28,568 --> 00:17:32,720
Yeah. You probably won't be
a cool boy anymore,

241
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:36,140
because you're going to
stay with that auntie!

242
00:17:36,140 --> 00:17:38,952
Please! Why would you believe Four and King?

243
00:17:38,952 --> 00:17:40,264
Don't listen to them, Sun.

244
00:17:40,264 --> 00:17:43,184
Yeah, don't listen to them, Sun.

245
00:17:44,980 --> 00:17:47,000
You can put it here.

246
00:17:47,780 --> 00:17:49,248
It's you again.

247
00:17:49,248 --> 00:17:50,872
You really get me.

248
00:17:50,872 --> 00:17:54,296
Thank you so much for asking them
to pack it nicely in this box.

249
00:17:54,296 --> 00:17:56,040
[Ploysai Seafood]
Of course.

250
00:17:56,220 --> 00:18:00,232
We can't leave strong-smelling food in the car
for too long.

251
00:18:02,709 --> 00:18:04,640
Leave it in the car for too long?

252
00:18:04,640 --> 00:18:07,230
I get you, Jee.

253
00:18:07,230 --> 00:18:11,900
Now it's your turn to get me.

254
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:14,960
Please take me to see Pobmek at the office.

255
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:19,780
Oh, the office is kind of complicated.

256
00:18:19,780 --> 00:18:20,808
There are a lot of people,

257
00:18:20,808 --> 00:18:22,160
you have to take the elevator up
several floors,

258
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:24,070
and you even need an employee badge.

259
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:25,980
Can I take you there another day?

260
00:18:25,980 --> 00:18:29,024
Jee, I'm begging you.

261
00:18:34,030 --> 00:18:36,820
Ever since Pobmek started university,

262
00:18:36,820 --> 00:18:39,720
he's been distant from me.

263
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:43,300
I know less about him every day.

264
00:18:43,300 --> 00:18:46,540
I'm scared that one day,

265
00:18:46,540 --> 00:18:50,072
I won't know anything about my son at all.

266
00:19:03,660 --> 00:19:05,032
Alright.

267
00:19:05,950 --> 00:19:08,200
I'll take you there.

268
00:19:10,460 --> 00:19:12,232
Thank you so much.

269
00:19:12,232 --> 00:19:13,584
Let's go.

270
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:20,480
[Stop - Visitor Registration]

271
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:24,480
What can I help you with?

272
00:19:25,386 --> 00:19:27,784
Oh, are you new?

273
00:19:27,784 --> 00:19:29,410
Why don't you recognize me?

274
00:19:29,410 --> 00:19:32,896
I'm one of the auditors.

275
00:19:35,750 --> 00:19:37,936
Can I just drive in and out in 10 minutes?

276
00:19:37,936 --> 00:19:39,728
I'll be quick.

277
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:58,740
Their security system is great, isn't it?

278
00:19:58,740 --> 00:20:00,904
They keep checking over and over.

279
00:20:01,780 --> 00:20:04,404
You can tap your employee badge here.

280
00:20:05,505 --> 00:20:07,460
I forgot my badge.

281
00:20:07,460 --> 00:20:08,510
What should I do?

282
00:20:08,510 --> 00:20:09,760
It's okay.

283
00:20:09,760 --> 00:20:11,992
This is my son's business card.

284
00:20:11,992 --> 00:20:13,688
He works here.

285
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:20,704
This looks like it's not...

286
00:20:26,620 --> 00:20:28,730
Jee!

287
00:20:28,730 --> 00:20:30,864
What have you done?

288
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:33,740
You drove into the barrier?

289
00:20:33,740 --> 00:20:34,912
Are you out of your mind?

290
00:20:34,912 --> 00:20:36,104
I'm sorry.

291
00:20:36,104 --> 00:20:38,304
I didn't know what to do and freaked out.

292
00:20:38,304 --> 00:20:39,440
Fine.

293
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:40,980
Just do whatever you can

294
00:20:40,980 --> 00:20:42,664
to keep her from causing any more trouble.

295
00:20:42,664 --> 00:20:45,150
And don't let our secret get out,
no matter what.

296
00:20:45,150 --> 00:20:46,464
- Got it?
- Yeah.

297
00:20:46,464 --> 00:20:48,261
I'll be right there.

298
00:20:52,740 --> 00:20:53,776
You see, Sun?

299
00:20:53,776 --> 00:20:55,288
The truth is out.

300
00:20:55,288 --> 00:20:57,800
He really wants to get rid of you.

301
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:06,672
Jee, I figured it out.

302
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:10,256
You're a teacher,

303
00:21:10,256 --> 00:21:13,650
but you didn't tell your family, did you?

304
00:21:13,650 --> 00:21:16,440
Wait, how do you know?

305
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:19,600
[School Vehicle Access Card]

306
00:21:25,260 --> 00:21:28,160
And you want
to hide it from your parents, right?

307
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:31,472
I bet you're afraid they'll be disappointed.

308
00:21:33,240 --> 00:21:35,830
I think I get it.

309
00:21:35,830 --> 00:21:37,576
You're a grown-up.

310
00:21:37,576 --> 00:21:41,530
It's normal to have secrets.

311
00:21:41,530 --> 00:21:42,712
How about this?

312
00:21:42,712 --> 00:21:46,620
I won't make a big deal out of it, okay?

313
00:21:46,620 --> 00:21:49,100
Is it going to be a big deal?

314
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:51,016
How could it not be?

315
00:21:51,016 --> 00:21:55,608
I hate it so much when adults keep secrets.

316
00:21:55,608 --> 00:21:58,380
It's bad, bad, bad.

317
00:22:01,110 --> 00:22:02,632
Oh! Hey!

318
00:22:02,632 --> 00:22:04,450
Where are you going?

319
00:22:04,450 --> 00:22:05,640
I'll tell you later.

320
00:22:05,640 --> 00:22:07,344
Take care of Sun for me.

321
00:22:08,664 --> 00:22:10,184
What's going on?

322
00:22:11,112 --> 00:22:13,520
Why is Uncle doing this to me?

323
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:15,070
Why does he want me
to stay with someone else?

324
00:22:15,070 --> 00:22:18,320
Looks like you'll have to do
what fairytale princesses do.

325
00:22:18,320 --> 00:22:20,430
Huh? What's he supposed to do?

326
00:22:20,430 --> 00:22:21,720
Run away, of course.

327
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:24,048
What are you waiting for, Sun?

328
00:22:35,890 --> 00:22:37,750
Are you okay?

329
00:22:37,750 --> 00:22:39,180
I'm fine.

330
00:22:39,180 --> 00:22:42,040
But your mom already left.

331
00:22:42,040 --> 00:22:44,632
She said she didn't want
the crab meat she bought to go bad.

332
00:22:46,137 --> 00:22:48,004
What's all this?

333
00:22:48,820 --> 00:22:52,360
Pobmek, tell me honestly.

334
00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:55,352
How much longer are you going to
keep lying to your mom?

335
00:22:56,450 --> 00:23:00,344
When she found out I was just a teacher,
she didn't seem to mind.

336
00:23:05,912 --> 00:23:08,360
- Hello?
- Hey! We have a problem!

337
00:23:08,360 --> 00:23:10,350
Sun ran away from school!

338
00:23:10,350 --> 00:23:11,456
- What?
- What is it?

339
00:23:11,456 --> 00:23:12,880
I already asked the kids.

340
00:23:12,880 --> 00:23:14,776
They said Sun's heading back to the condo.

341
00:23:14,776 --> 00:23:17,380
Damn! What the hell?

342
00:23:17,380 --> 00:23:18,560
Hey, what's going on?

343
00:23:18,560 --> 00:23:20,120
My mom is about to meet Sun!

344
00:23:20,120 --> 00:23:21,688
Shit!

345
00:23:28,928 --> 00:23:31,888
Oh, you're back.

346
00:23:33,090 --> 00:23:34,424
Yeah.

347
00:23:39,910 --> 00:23:42,820
Hey. What are you looking for?

348
00:23:42,820 --> 00:23:45,904
Oh, nothing.

349
00:23:47,490 --> 00:23:48,550
Uncle!

350
00:23:48,550 --> 00:23:51,384
You can't just ship me off to some auntie!

351
00:23:56,460 --> 00:23:57,944
And who's this auntie?

352
00:23:57,944 --> 00:24:00,056
Are you going to steal my bed?

353
00:24:18,830 --> 00:24:23,580
So you're telling me that after the accident,

354
00:24:23,580 --> 00:24:26,576
Solar has been like this?

355
00:24:27,616 --> 00:24:30,420
It might sound hard to believe,

356
00:24:31,100 --> 00:24:33,576
but as you can see,

357
00:24:33,576 --> 00:24:38,088
my friends and I are trying to
help Solar recover.

358
00:24:39,900 --> 00:24:41,958
So...

359
00:24:42,979 --> 00:24:45,592
please don't be mad at him.

360
00:24:47,900 --> 00:24:49,688
Is this why...

361
00:24:51,058 --> 00:24:56,863
you've been avoiding me all this time?

362
00:25:00,410 --> 00:25:01,742
Well...

363
00:25:02,801 --> 00:25:08,152
I was just afraid... you wouldn't understand.

364
00:25:13,404 --> 00:25:16,518
We're family.

365
00:25:19,128 --> 00:25:21,930
You're not the only one who's grown up.

366
00:25:24,264 --> 00:25:27,060
Things I couldn't accept before,

367
00:25:28,820 --> 00:25:32,448
I understand better now.

368
00:25:48,590 --> 00:25:52,200
We haven't gotten to know each other yet.

369
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:53,936
My name is Pafun.

370
00:25:53,936 --> 00:25:56,021
And you?

371
00:25:56,021 --> 00:25:57,872
What's your name?

372
00:25:58,820 --> 00:26:00,470
It's Sun.

373
00:26:00,470 --> 00:26:02,810
Sun is very mature for his age.

374
00:26:02,810 --> 00:26:06,080
Just a little naughty.

375
00:26:06,080 --> 00:26:07,750
I'm not naughty!

376
00:26:07,750 --> 00:26:10,456
Actually, I'm a very good kid,

377
00:26:10,456 --> 00:26:11,944
and I work hard at school.

378
00:26:11,944 --> 00:26:13,490
Right, Uncle?

379
00:26:13,490 --> 00:26:15,840
Yeah. If you say so.

380
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:20,104
But it'd be great if you spoke more politely.

381
00:26:21,770 --> 00:26:26,221
But I think the good thing about being a kid

382
00:26:26,221 --> 00:26:28,952
is being able to speak directly,

383
00:26:28,952 --> 00:26:32,780
not beating around the bush like adults.

384
00:26:32,780 --> 00:26:38,870
Besides, I don't think you're stubborn,
right?

385
00:26:38,870 --> 00:26:40,350
That's right.

386
00:26:40,350 --> 00:26:43,760
The stubborn one is the one teaching.

387
00:26:48,180 --> 00:26:50,440
Look, Auntie!

388
00:26:50,440 --> 00:26:54,552
He's a teacher, but he's even
more stubborn than his students.

389
00:27:11,750 --> 00:27:13,193
Pobmek.

390
00:27:15,174 --> 00:27:16,464
You...

391
00:27:19,446 --> 00:27:21,086
You're...

392
00:27:23,240 --> 00:27:27,656
You're not... an auditor?

393
00:27:30,410 --> 00:27:32,000
I was.

394
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:33,560
And?

395
00:27:34,970 --> 00:27:36,790
Now you're a teacher?

396
00:27:36,790 --> 00:27:39,048
Teaching elementary students?

397
00:27:40,250 --> 00:27:41,576
Yes.

398
00:27:46,100 --> 00:27:48,160
Go quit your job right now.

399
00:27:51,020 --> 00:27:52,625
Mom.

400
00:27:53,522 --> 00:27:55,279
- Calm down.
- Come with me!

401
00:27:55,279 --> 00:27:57,060
You're going to quit right now!

402
00:27:58,880 --> 00:28:01,300
I said right now! You hear me?

403
00:28:01,300 --> 00:28:03,270
Do you hear me?

404
00:28:03,270 --> 00:28:05,176
Pobmek, look at me!

405
00:28:05,176 --> 00:28:06,656
I said you need to quit right now!

406
00:28:06,656 --> 00:28:08,128
I won't allow this!

407
00:28:08,128 --> 00:28:09,280
You're coming with me!

408
00:28:09,280 --> 00:28:11,136
I'm not quitting!

409
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:16,776
Stop forcing me already, will you?

410
00:28:16,776 --> 00:28:17,920
I'm not forcing you.

411
00:28:17,920 --> 00:28:18,930
You are.

412
00:28:18,930 --> 00:28:21,400
Fine! I'm forcing you!

413
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:25,170
Am I so wrong for wanting my son
to have a good future?

414
00:28:25,170 --> 00:28:27,224
What's wrong with my life right now?

415
00:28:27,224 --> 00:28:30,016
How is being a teacher a bad thing?

416
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:37,400
Jee is a teacher just like me.

417
00:28:38,450 --> 00:28:41,110
We even teach at the same school.

418
00:28:41,110 --> 00:28:44,610
Why aren't you scolding Jee,
but you're scolding me?

419
00:28:44,610 --> 00:28:46,896
How are Jee and I any different?

420
00:28:51,510 --> 00:28:53,126
In the end...

421
00:28:55,100 --> 00:28:57,360
you're kind to everyone,

422
00:28:58,560 --> 00:29:00,960
except your own son.

423
00:29:17,580 --> 00:29:21,232
Uncle, where are you taking me?

424
00:29:32,752 --> 00:29:36,680
Uncle, where are we going?

425
00:29:41,792 --> 00:29:43,230
Uncle.

426
00:29:45,340 --> 00:29:46,420
Uncle.

427
00:29:46,420 --> 00:29:48,360
Uncle, I'm scared.

428
00:30:32,880 --> 00:30:35,528
♫ Let our story be written in our hearts ♫

429
00:30:35,528 --> 00:30:37,928
♫ 'Cause this love is meant just for us ♫

430
00:30:37,928 --> 00:30:42,440
♫ I will never let your hand go ♫

431
00:30:42,440 --> 00:30:45,128
♫ I will paint
and fill the storyline with you ♫

432
00:30:45,128 --> 00:30:48,096
♫ No matter if the sky turns dark and blue ♫

433
00:30:48,096 --> 00:30:53,008
♫ I will remain right here beside you,
always ♫

434
00:30:53,008 --> 00:30:54,680
Pobmek!

435
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:12,380
Didn't you have an interview today?

436
00:31:12,380 --> 00:31:14,240
Why didn't you go?

437
00:31:16,260 --> 00:31:19,376
You gave it up for music? Seriously?

438
00:32:53,530 --> 00:32:55,050
Wanna do it now?

439
00:32:55,050 --> 00:32:58,770
Come on! No more.

440
00:32:58,770 --> 00:33:01,200
We've been at it all day.

441
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:02,976
No!

442
00:33:07,830 --> 00:33:11,430
I mean, when are you
going to pack your stuff?

443
00:33:11,430 --> 00:33:13,264
We have to move out tomorrow.

444
00:33:13,264 --> 00:33:15,670
Yeah, I know.

445
00:33:15,670 --> 00:33:17,600
We still have time tomorrow.

446
00:33:20,960 --> 00:33:24,360
[Whose boyfriend is this?]

447
00:33:25,419 --> 00:33:26,760
What are you up to?

448
00:33:26,760 --> 00:33:28,341
Nothing.

449
00:33:29,156 --> 00:33:31,274
I just wanted to show off my boyfriend.

450
00:33:37,906 --> 00:33:38,900
Hey!

451
00:33:38,900 --> 00:33:41,640
What are you doing?

452
00:33:41,640 --> 00:33:43,608
I give up! I get it!

453
00:33:43,608 --> 00:33:44,940
I get it!

454
00:33:44,940 --> 00:33:47,910
Don't be so naughty, okay?

455
00:33:47,910 --> 00:33:49,896
No! Stop!

456
00:33:49,896 --> 00:33:51,304
Stop!

457
00:33:57,970 --> 00:34:00,460
- Hey.
- Yeah?

458
00:34:00,460 --> 00:34:03,000
There's one thing I still don't understand.

459
00:34:04,860 --> 00:34:08,656
Why did you stop playing guitar?

460
00:34:16,510 --> 00:34:20,312
I just didn't want to play anymore.

461
00:34:21,220 --> 00:34:22,656
Really?

462
00:34:24,140 --> 00:34:25,888
That's a shame.

463
00:34:30,990 --> 00:34:32,480
Look.

464
00:34:37,210 --> 00:34:41,616
When you're with a guitar, you look happy.

465
00:35:00,630 --> 00:35:02,016
Hey!

466
00:35:02,850 --> 00:35:04,648
What's wrong?

467
00:36:24,616 --> 00:36:26,288
Wow!

468
00:36:27,500 --> 00:36:29,992
You're such a sigma boy, Uncle!

469
00:36:32,270 --> 00:36:36,020
Sun, I can play the guitar now!

470
00:36:36,020 --> 00:36:37,248
I can do it now!

471
00:36:37,248 --> 00:36:39,320
Yay!

472
00:36:39,320 --> 00:36:42,024
I can do it now! Yay!

473
00:36:42,990 --> 00:36:44,688
Yay!

474
00:36:46,070 --> 00:36:47,720
Uncle, watch out!

475
00:36:47,720 --> 00:36:50,560
[Pobmek]

476
00:36:56,500 --> 00:36:58,360
Hello?

477
00:36:59,780 --> 00:37:02,980
Yes, he's my son.

478
00:37:02,980 --> 00:37:04,368
What?

479
00:37:05,080 --> 00:37:07,192
He's in the hospital?

480
00:37:23,648 --> 00:37:25,344
Pobmek.

481
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:30,544
I'm sorry.

482
00:37:31,900 --> 00:37:34,048
It's my fault.

483
00:37:35,120 --> 00:37:39,469
I never realized...

484
00:37:41,036 --> 00:37:45,391
that I'd been hurting you your whole life.

485
00:37:57,620 --> 00:37:58,855
Oh?

486
00:37:59,740 --> 00:38:03,064
But they said you were in the hospital.

487
00:38:04,120 --> 00:38:06,152
I just came to get my finger treated.

488
00:38:16,810 --> 00:38:20,640
I was sitting on the side of the road

489
00:38:20,640 --> 00:38:22,838
when a car grazed me.

490
00:38:23,660 --> 00:38:25,584
But I'm fine.

491
00:38:28,870 --> 00:38:32,270
What didn't survive was the guitar.

492
00:38:32,270 --> 00:38:34,440
It got completely crushed.

493
00:38:36,740 --> 00:38:38,426
So...

494
00:38:39,760 --> 00:38:42,296
you're still playing guitar?

495
00:38:43,670 --> 00:38:47,040
I actually just got back into it.

496
00:38:49,140 --> 00:38:52,112
I have to, especially now.

497
00:38:55,870 --> 00:38:59,736
Because it's the only way
that can help Solar recover.

498
00:39:06,070 --> 00:39:07,409
Mom.

499
00:39:09,696 --> 00:39:12,500
Could you please be a little kinder to me?

500
00:39:14,344 --> 00:39:16,528
Both about the guitar...

501
00:39:18,420 --> 00:39:20,672
and about me being a teacher.

502
00:39:21,910 --> 00:39:24,424
It might not be what you want,

503
00:39:25,860 --> 00:39:28,488
but it's what I truly chose for myself.

504
00:39:38,690 --> 00:39:41,344
I'm sorry.

505
00:39:41,344 --> 00:39:44,140
I was really wrong.

506
00:39:47,120 --> 00:39:49,595
From now on,

507
00:39:49,595 --> 00:39:52,310
I won't stop you from doing anything.

508
00:39:54,380 --> 00:39:56,624
I promise.

509
00:40:06,890 --> 00:40:10,538
That's not how you make a promise.

510
00:40:11,980 --> 00:40:16,050
Then how do you make one?

511
00:40:16,050 --> 00:40:18,016
You have to pinky promise.

512
00:40:20,488 --> 00:40:21,808
Alright, come on.

513
00:40:21,808 --> 00:40:24,064
Let's pinky promise.

514
00:40:33,260 --> 00:40:36,096
No. I changed my mind.

515
00:40:36,096 --> 00:40:38,568
Let's hug!

516
00:40:54,832 --> 00:41:00,140
You'll see what Pobmek is like as a teacher.

517
00:41:00,140 --> 00:41:03,940
He might not be perfect,
but he's pretty good.

518
00:41:03,940 --> 00:41:05,656
- Okay.
- 8 times 12?

519
00:41:05,656 --> 00:41:07,368
- 96!
- Good job!

520
00:41:07,368 --> 00:41:09,100
Give yourselves a big hand!

521
00:41:09,100 --> 00:41:11,016
Next, let's do the 9 times table.
I've already taught you this.

522
00:41:11,016 --> 00:41:12,416
I know you all can do it.

523
00:41:12,416 --> 00:41:14,248
- 9 times 1?
- 9!

524
00:41:14,248 --> 00:41:16,048
- 9 times 2?
- Still good!

525
00:41:16,048 --> 00:41:18,544
- 9 times 3?
- Our brains are on fire!

526
00:41:18,544 --> 00:41:20,096
Heh!

527
00:41:21,300 --> 00:41:22,608
Oh.

528
00:41:23,820 --> 00:41:25,920
Guys, this is my mom.

529
00:41:25,920 --> 00:41:32,500
- Say hello.
- Hello, ma'am!

530
00:41:32,500 --> 00:41:33,760
Thank you.

531
00:41:33,760 --> 00:41:37,168
Here, I have something for you.

532
00:41:43,080 --> 00:41:45,880
Wow!

533
00:41:49,390 --> 00:41:52,776
Teacher, can you play a song for us?

534
00:41:52,776 --> 00:41:58,376
Play a song!

535
00:41:58,376 --> 00:41:59,400
Alright.

536
00:41:59,400 --> 00:42:01,688
I'll play one song, but you have to
get back to studying after that, okay?

537
00:42:01,688 --> 00:42:04,312
Yay!

538
00:42:36,950 --> 00:42:38,150
Hey.

539
00:42:38,150 --> 00:42:40,520
What if Solar doesn't recover?

540
00:42:40,520 --> 00:42:44,688
Do you two really think you'll be okay?

541
00:42:45,780 --> 00:42:47,550
Mom!

542
00:42:47,550 --> 00:42:49,096
You're ruining the mood.

543
00:42:49,096 --> 00:42:53,424
Hey, I'm really not judging.

544
00:42:53,424 --> 00:42:56,740
I'm just worried about you.

545
00:42:56,740 --> 00:43:01,136
If that's the case,
I'll help take care of him.

546
00:43:01,880 --> 00:43:04,190
Thank you so much, Aunt.

547
00:43:04,190 --> 00:43:07,980
Honestly, it's because of Pobmek

548
00:43:07,980 --> 00:43:12,984
that I want to do everything I can
to get better.

549
00:43:17,300 --> 00:43:19,592
Hey, Pobmek.

550
00:43:21,110 --> 00:43:23,120
Why don't you play that special song for me?

551
00:43:23,120 --> 00:43:26,903
The one you said could make Sun
fall asleep right away.

552
00:43:26,903 --> 00:43:28,664
I want to hear it.

553
00:43:31,940 --> 00:43:35,030
I still can't really remember that one,

554
00:43:35,030 --> 00:43:39,410
but I do remember
it's a song I wrote when I was in a band.

555
00:43:39,410 --> 00:43:42,696
It's okay. Just play whatever you can.

556
00:44:01,900 --> 00:44:03,440
Mom!

557
00:44:03,440 --> 00:44:04,808
No filming! I'm shy!

558
00:44:04,808 --> 00:44:06,568
Don't be shy. Keep playing.

559
00:44:06,568 --> 00:44:09,024
This is your moment.

560
00:44:09,740 --> 00:44:12,432
Solar, I'll send you the clip later.

561
00:44:12,432 --> 00:44:14,216
Thank you.

562
00:44:16,780 --> 00:44:18,296
Cute.

563
00:44:22,760 --> 00:44:26,320
[Solar: Mom, I have something to show you!]

564
00:44:29,420 --> 00:44:32,720
I'm glad you and your mom made up.
[Atsara & Little Lion]

565
00:44:32,720 --> 00:44:34,460
You seem totally different now.

566
00:44:34,460 --> 00:44:36,240
Really?

567
00:44:37,270 --> 00:44:40,060
Since I met you,

568
00:44:40,060 --> 00:44:43,792
it's felt like
you've always been carrying something.

569
00:44:45,726 --> 00:44:49,398
But today, right now,

570
00:44:50,676 --> 00:44:52,790
you've finally put it down.

571
00:44:56,814 --> 00:45:00,000
That's probably true.

572
00:45:00,000 --> 00:45:04,672
Mom and I are just starting to understand...

573
00:45:05,969 --> 00:45:08,587
and learn more about each other.

574
00:45:09,654 --> 00:45:12,456
I guess that's life.

575
00:45:14,483 --> 00:45:17,500
There's so much more to learn.

576
00:45:17,500 --> 00:45:20,688
Wow. Well said.

577
00:45:23,393 --> 00:45:27,701
I'm so lucky to have you as my boyfriend.

578
00:45:31,713 --> 00:45:33,677
Let me kiss your cheek.

579
00:45:45,426 --> 00:45:49,950
I'm just as lucky
to have you as my boyfriend.

580
00:46:13,100 --> 00:46:15,248
Why do you want Sun to sleep so much?

581
00:46:15,248 --> 00:46:17,180
Because I'm tired of him.

582
00:46:17,180 --> 00:46:18,872
Sodchuen, has anyone seen Sun?

583
00:46:18,872 --> 00:46:23,888
Today, we're on a secret mission
to take Sun to his mom!

584
00:46:23,888 --> 00:46:25,120
What?

585
00:46:25,120 --> 00:46:26,770
What now?

586
00:46:26,770 --> 00:46:28,096
Sun! Sun.

587
00:46:28,096 --> 00:46:29,470
Hey!

588
00:46:29,470 --> 00:46:32,192
Aunt, what is this?

589
00:46:33,170 --> 00:46:37,900
I'm just wondering
if all of this is my fault.

590
00:46:37,900 --> 00:46:39,848
But you still have me.

